## ğŸ¯ Overview

**Smart Expense Tracker** is a comprehensive, console-based financial management application designed for individuals, freelancers, and small businesses who want to efficiently track, categorize, and analyze their daily expenses.

### Why Smart Expense Tracker?

- âœ… **Lightweight**: No bloated frameworks, pure Java with JDBC
- âœ… **Professional**: Industry-standard design patterns and best practices
- âœ… **Complete**: Full CRUD operations with advanced features
- âœ… **Secure**: SQL injection prevention, input validation
- âœ… **Scalable**: Layered architecture ready for expansion
- âœ… **Educational**: Perfect for learning Java, JDBC, and database design

### Key Benefits

| Benefit | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| ğŸ’° **Financial Awareness** | Understand your spending patterns |
| ğŸ“Š **Detailed Analytics** | Monthly summaries and category-wise reports |
| ğŸ“ **Data Export** | CSV export for spreadsheet compatibility |
| ğŸ”’ **Data Security** | Database-backed persistence with encryption-ready |
| âš¡ **Performance** | Indexed database queries for fast retrieval |
| ğŸ“ **Learning Tool** | Great for mastering Java and databases |

---

## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ’° Expense Management
- **Add Expenses**: Record expenses with description, amount, date, category, payment method, and notes
- **View All**: Display all expenses in a formatted table
- **Update**: Modify existing expense details
- **Delete**: Remove expenses with confirmation
- **Search**: Find expenses by keyword

### ğŸ” Advanced Filtering
- Filter by **category** (Food, Transport, Utilities, etc.)
- Filter by **date range** (custom start and end dates)
- Filter by **month and year** (e.g., November 2025)
- Filter by **description** (keyword search)

### ğŸ”„ Flexible Sorting
- Sort by **date** (newest/oldest first)
- Sort by **amount** (highest/lowest first)
- Combined sorting with filtering

### ğŸ“Š Comprehensive Reporting
- **Monthly Summary**: Total, count, average, min/max expenses
- **Category-wise Report**: Spending breakdown by category with percentages
- **Budget Status**: Track spending against category budgets
- **Year-to-Date**: Annual spending totals
- **Trend Analysis**: Month-over-month comparisons

### ğŸ“¥ Data Export
- **CSV Export**: Export all or filtered expenses
- **Custom Filenames**: Timestamped or user-defined
- **Proper Formatting**: Handles special characters correctly
- **Excel Compatible**: Opens directly in spreadsheet apps

### ğŸ“‚ Category Management
- **10 Predefined Categories**: Food & Dining, Transportation, Utilities, Healthcare, Entertainment, Shopping, Education, Rent, Savings, Others
- **Budget Limits**: Set spending limits per category
- **Budget Alerts**: Track spending vs budget
- **Extensible**: Easy to add new categories

### âœ”ï¸ Validation & Security
- Comprehensive input validation
- SQL injection prevention (PreparedStatement)
- Amount validation (positive values)
- Date validation (no future dates)
- Category validation (enforces valid categories)
- Exception handling throughout

### ğŸ¨ User Experience
- Clean, formatted console UI
- Numbered menu options
- Color-coded messages (âœ“, âŒ, ğŸ’°)
- Confirmation prompts for destructive operations
- Helpful error messages

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technology Stack

### Core Technologies
| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| **Java** | 11+ | Programming language |
| **JDBC** | 4.2+ | Database connectivity |
| **MySQL** | 8.0+ | Database management |
| **Maven** | 3.6+ | Build tool (optional) |

### Java Features Used
- **OOP**: Inheritance, Encapsulation, Polymorphism, Abstraction
- **Collections**: ArrayList, HashMap, LinkedHashMap, Streams
- **Streams API**: Filtering, sorting, mapping
- **Date/Time API**: LocalDate for date handling
- **Exception Handling**: Try-catch, custom exceptions, try-with-resources
- **File I/O**: CSV export functionality
- **JDBC**: Connection management, PreparedStatement, ResultSet

### Design Patterns
- **Singleton Pattern**: DatabaseConnection ensures single connection
- **DAO Pattern**: ExpenseDAO abstracts database operations
- **Service Layer Pattern**: Business logic separation
- **Factory Pattern**: (Extensible for different expense types)

