## ğŸš€ Installation

### Step 1: Clone or Download Repository

```bash
# Using Git
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/SmartExpenseTracker.git
cd SmartExpenseTracker

# Or download and extract ZIP file
unzip SmartExpenseTracker.zip
cd SmartExpenseTracker
```

### Step 2: Install Java (if not installed)

**Windows:**
1. Download from [OpenJDK](https://adoptium.net/) or [Oracle](https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/)
2. Run installer
3. Set JAVA_HOME environment variable

**macOS:**
```bash
brew install openjdk@11
```

**Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):**
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk
```

### Step 3: Install MySQL (if not installed)

**Windows:**
1. Download MySQL Installer from [mysql.com](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/)
2. Run installer and configure

**macOS:**
```bash
brew install mysql
brew services start mysql
```

**Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):**
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install mysql-server
sudo systemctl start mysql
```

### Step 4: Create Project Structure

```bash
# Create directories
mkdir -p src/com/expensetracker/{main,model,database,service,utils,exception}
mkdir -p lib exports bin

# Copy all source files to appropriate directories
# (See project structure below)
```

### Step 5: Download MySQL Connector

1. Visit: [MySQL Connector/J Download](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/)
2. Select **Platform Independent** â†’ **ZIP Archive**
3. Extract `mysql-connector-java-8.0.33.jar`
4. Place in `lib/` directory

### Step 6: Setup Database

```bash
# Run database schema
mysql -u root -p < schema.sql

# Or manually
mysql -u root -p
mysql> SOURCE schema.sql;
mysql> USE smart_expense_tracker;
mysql> SHOW TABLES;
mysql> EXIT;
```

### Step 7: Configure Credentials

Edit `src/com/expensetracker/database/DatabaseConnection.java`:

```java
private static final String DB_USER = "root";              // Your username
private static final String DB_PASSWORD = "your_password"; // Your password
```

### Step 8: Compile

```bash
# Windows
javac -d bin -cp "lib\*" src\com\expensetracker\**\*.java

# Linux/macOS
javac -d bin -cp "lib/*" src/com/expensetracker/**/*.java
```

### Step 9: Run

```bash
# Windows
java -cp "bin;lib\*" com.expensetracker.main.App

# Linux/macOS
java -cp "bin:lib/*" com.expensetracker.main.App
```

---

## âš¡ Quick Start

### Using Runner Scripts

**Windows:**
```cmd
# First time: compile
run.bat compile

# Run application
run.bat
```

**Linux/macOS:**
```bash
# Make executable
chmod +x run.sh

# First time: compile
./run.sh compile

# Run application
./run.sh
```

### First Use

```
1. Add some expenses
2. View all expenses
3. Generate monthly report
4. Export to CSV
5. Try different filters and sorts
```

