## ğŸ’» Code Examples

### Example 1: Adding an Expense Programmatically

```java
ExpenseService expenseService = new ExpenseService();

boolean success = expenseService.createExpense(
    "Grocery Shopping",      // description
    1500.00,                 // amount
    LocalDate.now(),         // date
    "Food & Dining",         // category
    "Debit Card",            // payment method
    "Weekly groceries"       // notes
);

if (success) {
    System.out.println("âœ“ Expense added successfully!");
}
```

### Example 2: Filtering Expenses

```java
// Filter by category
List<Expense> foodExpenses = expenseService.filterByCategory("Food & Dining");

// Filter by date range
LocalDate start = LocalDate.of(2025, 11, 1);
LocalDate end = LocalDate.of(2025, 11, 30);
List<Expense> monthExpenses = expenseService.filterByDateRange(start, end);

// Sort by amount
List<Expense> sorted = expenseService.sortByAmountDescending();
```

### Example 3: Generating Reports

```java
ReportService reportService = new ReportService();

// Monthly summary
Map<String, Object> summary = reportService.getMonthlySummary(11, 2025);
System.out.println("Total: " + summary.get("total_expenses"));

// Category-wise report
Map<String, Double> categoryReport = reportService.getCategoryWiseReport();
for (Map.Entry<String, Double> entry : categoryReport.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println(entry.getKey() + ": â‚¹" + entry.getValue());
}

// Display formatted reports
reportService.printCategoryReport();
```

### Example 4: CSV Export

```java
CSVExporter exporter = new CSVExporter();

// Export all expenses
List<Expense> allExpenses = expenseService.getAllExpenses();
String filename = exporter.exportToCSV(allExpenses);
System.out.println("Exported to: " + filename);

// Export filtered expenses
List<Expense> filtered = expenseService.filterByMonth(11, 2025);
exporter.exportToCSV(filtered, "november_2025_expenses");
```

---

## âš¡ Performance

### Time Complexity Analysis

| Operation | Complexity | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Add Expense | O(1) | Single INSERT query |
| View All | O(n) | SELECT all records, n = total expenses |
| Filter by Category | O(n) | WHERE clause filters n records |
| Sort by Amount | O(n log n) | In-memory Timsort algorithm |
| Monthly Summary | O(n) | Single pass aggregation |
| Category Report | O(n) | HashMap aggregation, k = categories |

### Space Complexity

| Operation | Space | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| Load All Expenses | O(n) | Store n expenses in memory |
| Filter Results | O(m) | m = matching records |
| Category Report | O(k) | k = unique categories |
| Sort Results | O(n) | New sorted list created |

### Optimization Tips

1. **Use Database Filtering** for large datasets instead of in-memory filtering
2. **Add Indexes** on frequently queried columns (expense_date, category)
3. **Pagination** for loading large result sets
4. **Connection Pooling** for multiple concurrent users
5. **Query Caching** for frequently generated reports

